> Tip: Welcome to your space
> This is your personal space, and you can do whatever you want with it.
> You could use it to:
>
>
> Create a to-do list
>
>
> Capture rough ideas
>
>
> Store files or useful links
>
>
> Post pictures of your favorite gifs
>
>
> But those are just suggestions. Use it however you'd like.
> If you'd prefer, you can change the space permissions so nobody else can access this space. Or keep your space open, and add restrictions to individual pages that you want to keep private.
> To start, you might want to:
>
>
> Customise this overview using the edit icon at the top right of this page.
>
>
> Create a new page by clicking the + in the space sidebar.

content:
1. Open "StoreClosingTransferFile" and run the queries  up to the first SP in the script.
2. Go to this SP -> "gnc.[transfer].[SetItemsInformationCache]" and comment out two lines starting with "WHERE SeasonID .."(right above "DROP TABLE #PG"), select all with ctrl+A and execute with ctrl+E to save the SP. Then go back to original query and execute this SP.
3. Then go to Products tab on Legacy UI. Click "Get Selected Products" -> "save selection"
4. Then go to "Stores" tab on Legacy UI. Create a new scenario. You can choose a similar scenario (containing the word "clearance") as starting scenario.
5. Go back to SQL Server and continue from the store side (after the part where it says "product side is over")
6. Write your scenario name and store code to queries.

metadata.title: GNC - Store Transfer File Generation - Manual Steps

content:
he part where it says "product side is over")
6. Write your scenario name and store code to queries.
7. Go back to Stores tab on Legacy UI. Take the name of the bottom cluster (it is either "1", "CA_sfs", "Blocked", or something similar.)and write it to region = " " in third (or fourth if the store is in CA) query under store side. Run them until the SP (gnc.[transfer].[GetStoreRegionsForUI])
8. Go to that SP (gnc.[transfer].[GetStoreRegionsForUI]) and find this line -> "WHERE S.IsBlocked = 0 AND", and put "--" before "S.IsBlocked".
9. Go back to original query and execute that SP.
10. Go to Legacy UI and take our origin store and put the associated cluster with drag & drop. Click "Save scenario".
11. Follow the guidelines in "Store Region" option (on top of the page) if drag & drop does not work.
12. Go to "Runs" tab.
13. Date: Today's date. Tick Stock Clearance Run. Enter origin store to origin store box. Delete all stores in destination list and click save.

metadata.title: GNC - Store Transfer File Generation - Manual Steps

content:
e Run. Enter origin store to origin store box. Delete all stores in destination list and click save.
14. Enter a value to "Number of destinations for stock clearance" (or simply fill the destination list box with destination stores)
15. Tick optimize by region.
16. Double check the product count by browsing your pointer on "i" symbol above "Start a new run".
17. Write a comment and press "Start New Run".
18. Make final checks from UI and download the file by pressing excel icon on "Runs" tab.

After the run is completed:

1. Make your controls using the last queries at the bottom of original query. After that run the other check script.(StoreClearenceTransferResultsCheck.sql)
2. Revert those two SP (that you changed in step 2 and 8 back to original forms.

Note 1: It is better not to have more than 30 destination stores.
Note 2: Expected run time is 15-20 minutes.
Note 3: Transfer file generation run is not allowed during data transfer, wait DT to complete.

metadata.title: GNC - Store Transfer File Generation - Manual Steps
